  ('cml1au4ak006nx93xn8vkzr1k', 'Last Day on Earth: Survival', 'zombie.survival.craft.z', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=zombie.survival.craft.z', 'https://play-lh.googleusercontent.com/1NJaEmZal-WWfNTcpQkpO0Z0U4SbLMcit2K3DDW2_BQ7OJkyn1at4zDAgBGCfZLLubDd=s256-rw', 'https://ik.imagekit.io/yk0evs8op/games/zombie.survival.craft.z-icon_rlxkaaqdA.jpg', 'cml1au37f0000x93xcjfk9gjy', '[]', '4.0', '4.73M reviews', '4.73M reviews', NULL, 'Last Day on Earth is a multiplayer zombie survival action game with base building, crafting, and shooting zombies in a brutal post-apocalyptic world. Your life depends on how well you loot, craft, and build, turning whatever you find into weapons, gear, and a fortified shelter. Explore hostile lands, shoot zombies, and fight to protect everything you‚Äôve worked for. In this zombie survival world, every piece of loot matters, every wall you build matters, and every mistake may be your last.\n‚ñ† CRAFTING & BASE BUILDING\nSurvival begins with your two hands. You start alone and empty-handed, gathering basic resources to create tools, weapons, clothes, and the first components of what will be your shelter. Soon, that small shack becomes a fortified base with upgraded walls, traps, workbenches, and storages to keep your hard-earned loot safe. Crafting turns scraps into survival essentials ‚Äî from knives and guns to armor, explosives, medicine, and even vehicles. The durability of your shelter depends entirely on your ability to build and improve it, turning a fragile hideout into a real stronghold in a post-apocalyptic world.\n‚ñ† LOOTING A DEAD WORLD\nThe world around you is dangerous yet full of opportunity. You can explore forests, suburbs, military zones, toxic wastelands, and underground bunkers in search of materials that might boost your growth. Some areas provide simple resources, while others pose great danger, but allow you to secure rare components for advanced crafting and stronger defenses. Every trip outside the base becomes a calculated gamble: the more you dare, the better resources you bring home. Looting is more than just exploration ‚Äî it‚Äôs the fuel that keeps your shelter growing and your weapons ready for the next fight in this zombie survival action-adventure.\n‚ñ† SHOOT ZOMBIES & SURVIVE COMBAT\nThe undead never rest, and neither can you. You can craft melee weapons, firearms, and explosives, then adapt them to your playstyle ‚Äî quietly slicing through enemies or unleashing deafening firepower to wipe out entire hordes. As you progress, you modify weapons to increase their power, fire rate, range, and unique effects, making combat more strategic than just simple shooting. Combat here isn''t just about killing zombies; it''s about the intense action of defending your home and surviving the raids that turn most survivors into corpses. Encounter a variety of tough bosses in all sorts of weather conditions and win incredible rewards for your resilience and ingenuity.\nEven in the ruins of civilization, some things still help you survive:\n‚ñ† Pets like huskies and shepherds can join raids, carry extra loot, and help in combat, offering rare companionship in a dead world.\n‚ñ† Vehicles such as a Chopper, ATV, and motorboat allow you to reach remote territories filled with rare resources, which you‚Äôll need for advanced crafting and base upgrades.\n‚ñ† Clans & PvP at the Crater enable cooperation, trading, and competitive battles against other survivors and raiders ‚Äî teamwork can be beneficial, though it‚Äôs not required.\n‚ñ† Varied hostile locations ‚Äî police stations, farms, ports, bunkers, and infested areas conceal resources, secrets, and deadly enemies, each with their unique challenges and loot.\nIn a world where the dead rule and the living fight for scraps, and only those who build their shelter, loot the wasteland, and shoot their way forward will live long enough to see another sunrise.\nThe apocalypse isn‚Äôt coming ‚Äî it‚Äôs already here.', 'Fight th